-- African Union to Send 2,000 Troops to Somalia After Uganda Bombs, AFP Says
-- Renee Bonorchis
-- 2010-07-27T06:38:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/african-union-to-send-2-000-troops-to-somalia-after-uganda-bombs-afp-says.html

          
          
             African Union leaders agreed late
yesterday to send 2,000 more troops to Somalia, Agence France-
Presse reported, citing Ethiopian Foreign Minister  Seyoum Mesfin .  
 The AU wants to bolster its peacekeeping mission in Somalia
to counter al-Shabaab insurgents who claimed responsiblity for
two bomb attacks in Ugandaâ€™s capital Kampala on July 11 that
killed 76 people gathered to watch broadcasts of the soccer
World Cup final, the agency reported.  
